{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Image Decoding","modules":[{"name":"Nuke"}],"role":"article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Decoding","title":"Decoding","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingError","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke","doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/image-formats"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/image-decoding","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"ImageDecoding Protocol","anchor":"ImageDecoding-Protocol","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the core of the decoding infrastructure is the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["public protocol ImageDecoding: Sendable {","    \/\/\/ Returns `true` if you want the decoding to be performed on the","    \/\/\/ decoding queue. If `false`, decoding is performed synchronously","    \/\/\/ on the pipeline operation queue. By default, `true`.","    var isAsynchronous: Bool { get }","","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given image data.","    func decode(_ data: Data) throws -> ImageContainer","","    \/\/\/ Produces an image from the given partially downloaded image data.","    \/\/\/ This method might be called multiple times during a single decoding","    \/\/\/ session. When the image download is complete, ``decode(_:)`` is called.","    \/\/\/","    \/\/\/ - returns: nil by default.","    func decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_ data: Data) -> ImageContainer?","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" is a struct that wraps the decoded image and (optionally) the original data and some additional information. The decoder decides what to attach to the container."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["public struct ImageContainer {","    \/\/\/ Either `UIImage` or `NSImage`, depending on the platform.","    public var image: PlatformImage","    \/\/\/ An image type.","    public var type: AssetType?","    \/\/\/ Returns `true` if the image is a preview (progressive scan, thumbnail).","    public var isPreview: Bool","    \/\/\/ Contains the original image data, but only if the decoder attaches it.","    public var data: Data?","    \/\/\/ Metadata provided by the user.","    public var userInfo: [UserInfoKey: Any]","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the first chunk of the image data is loaded, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" creates a decoder for the given image format."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The pipeline uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to find the decoder.  The decoder is created once and is reused across a single image decoding session until the final chunk of data is downloaded. If the decoder supports progressive decoding, make it a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to retain state within a single decoding session."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decode(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method only passes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":" to the decoder. If the decoder needs additional information, pass it when instantiating it. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" provides everything that you might need, including the full "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also take advantage of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageRequest\/userInfo","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". For example, you may pass the target image view size to the SVG decoder to let it know the size of the image to create."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoding is performed in the background on the operation queue provided in "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/Configuration-swift.struct"},{"type":"text","text":". There is always only one decoding request at a time. The pipeline doesn’t call "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoding\/decodePartiallyDownloadedData(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" again until you are finished with the previous chunk."}]},{"text":"Registering Decoders","anchor":"Registering-Decoders","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To register the decoders, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoderRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func register() {","    ImageDecoderRegistry.shared.register(ImageDecoders.SVG.init)","}","","extension ImageDecoders {","    final class SVG: ImageDecoding {","        init?(context: ImageDecodingContext) {","            guard context.isCompleted else {","                return nil \/\/ No progressive decoding","            }","","            let isSVG = context.urlResponse?.url?.absoluteString.hasSuffix(\".svg\") ?? false","            guard isSVG else {","                return nil \/\/ Image format isn't supported.","            }   ","        }","    }","}"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To determine image type, use an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer that takes data as input. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/AssetType","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" represents uniform type identifiers or UTI."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"tip","name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you register a decoder, you have access to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecodingContext"},{"type":"text","text":" for the given decoding session."}]},{"text":"Rendering Engines","anchor":"Rendering-Engines","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The decoders in Nuke work at download time - regular decoders produce images as data arrives, while progressive decoders can produce multiple previews before delivering the final images. But there are scenarios when decoding at download time doesn’t work: for example, for animated images."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For animated images, it is not feasible to decode all of the frames and put them in memory as bitmaps at download time – it will consume too much memory. You have to postpone decoding to rendering time. When the image is displayed, a rendering engine, like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kaishin\/Gifu"},{"type":"text","text":" or others, will decode and cache image frames on demand."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GIF is not an efficient format. It is recommended to use short MP4 clips instead. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kean\/NukeDemo","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for an example."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"text":"Built-In Image Decoders","anchor":"Built-In-Image-Decoders","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can find all of the built-in decoders in the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders"},{"type":"text","text":" namespace."}]},{"text":"ImageDecoders.Default","anchor":"ImageDecodersDefault","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" is used by default if no custom decoders are registered. It uses native "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":" (and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSImage(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":") initializers to create images from data."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Default"},{"type":"text","text":" also supports progressive decoding via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGImageSourceCreateIncremental"},{"type":"text","text":". It produces previews as data arrives, gated by "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImagePipeline\/PreviewPolicy"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".incremental"},{"type":"text","text":" for progressive JPEGs and GIFs by default, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".disabled"},{"type":"text","text":" for other formats)."}]},{"text":"ImageDecoders.Video","anchor":"ImageDecodersVideo","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Generates a video preview and attaches downloaded data to the image container."}]},{"text":"ImageDecoders.Empty","anchor":"ImageDecodersEmpty","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" returns an empty placeholder image and attaches image data to the image container. It could also be configured to return partially downloaded data. "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.github.kean.nuke\/documentation\/Nuke\/ImageDecoders\/Empty"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used when the rendering engine works directly with image data."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nuke\/image-decoding"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"https://github.com/kean/NukeDemo":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/kean\/NukeDemo","title":"Nuke Demo","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/kean\/NukeDemo","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Nuke Demo"}]},"doc://com.github.kean.nuke/documentation/Nuke/ImageDecoders/Empty":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Empty","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A decoder that returns an empty placeholder image and attaches image"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text",